2:
You cover yourself with light as with a garment;
\q you spread out the heavens like a tent curtain.
\q

3:
You lay the beams of your chambers on the clouds;
\q you make the clouds your chariot;
\q you walk on the wings of the wind.

6:
You covered the earth with water like a garment;
\q the water covered the mountains.
\q

10:
He made springs flow into the valleys;
\q the streams flow between the mountains.
\q

11:
They supply water for all the animals of the field;
\q the wild donkeys quench their thirst.
\q

16:
The trees of Yahweh get plenty of rain;
\q the cedars of Lebanon which he planted.
\q

19:
He appointed the moon to mark the seasons;
\q the sun knows its time for setting.
\q

24:
Yahweh, how many and varied are your works!
\q With wisdom you made them all;
\q the earth overflows with your works.

31:
May the glory of Yahweh last forever;
\q may Yahweh enjoy his creation.
\q

33:
I will sing to Yahweh all my life;
\q I will sing praise to my God as long as I live.
\q
